<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>530 and DT-466/408 Diesel Engine Service (1994) - LUBRICATING OIL PUMP, OIL FILTER AND COOLER - LUBRICATING
        OIL PUMP - REASSEMBLY
    </stitle>
    <svcman/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="proctype" graphiccount="7">
        <title>REASSEMBLY</title>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Install a new crankshaft front oil seal into the lubricating oil pump housing as follows:
            </para>
            <step2>
                <para count="1">Apply gasket eliminator #515 to the O.D. of the oil seal.</para>
            </step2>
            <step2>
                <para count="1">Slip oil seal into installing tool.</para>
            </step2>
            <step2>
                <para count="1">Press the seal into the oil pump housing so the front of the seal is flush with the
                    front of the oil pump housing. Refer to
                    <emph type="bold">Figure
                        <hotlnk xrefid="ef1050911">9.11</hotlnk>
                    </emph>
                    .
                </para>
            </step2>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Install a new O-Ring on the front cover, then install the housing plate. Refer to
                <emph type="bold">Figure
                    <hotlnk xrefid="ef1050912">9.12</hotlnk>
                </emph>
                .
            </para>
            <figure id="ef1050911" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="eg2484" filename="../figeg2/EG2484.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 9.11.</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1>1. Press</callout1>
                    <callout1>2. Installation Tool</callout1>
                    <callout1>3. Oil Seal</callout1>
                    <callout1>4. Oil Pump Housing</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
            <figure id="ef1050912" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="eg2469" filename="../figeg2/EG2469.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 9.12.</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1>1. O-Ring</callout1>
                    <callout1>2. Oil Pump Plate</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Install the inner rotor and slinger onto the gear spline. Refer to
                <emph type="bold">Figure
                    <hotlnk xrefid="ef1050913">9.13</hotlnk>
                </emph>
                .
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">With the inner rotor installed, tap in the crankshaft key with a plastic hammer. Refer to
                <emph type="bold">Figure
                    <hotlnk xrefid="ef1050914">9.14</hotlnk>
                </emph>
                .
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Install the outer rotor into the housing. Lubricate the rotator with clean engine oil. Refer
                to
                <emph type="bold">Figure
                    <hotlnk xrefid="ef1050915">9.15</hotlnk>
                </emph>
                .
            </para>
            <specpara>
                <note>
                    <para>Slinger fits with the convex shape facing out.</para>
                </note>
            </specpara>
            <figure id="ef1050913" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="eg2471" filename="../figeg2/EG2471.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 9.13.</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1>1. Slinger</callout1>
                    <callout1>2. Crankshaft</callout1>
                    <callout1>3. Inner Rotor</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
            <figure id="ef1050914" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="eg2472" filename="../figeg2/EG2472.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 9.14.</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1>1. Crankshaft Key</callout1>
                    <callout1>2. Crankshaft</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
            <figure id="ef1050915" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="eg2473" filename="../figeg2/EG2473.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 9.15.</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1>1. Mounting Dowels</callout1>
                    <callout1>2. Outer Rotor</callout1>
                    <callout1>3. O-Ring Groove</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Install a new O-Ring into the housing groove and align housing dowel pins with mounting
                locations. Refer to
                <emph type="bold">Figure
                    <hotlnk xrefid="ef1050916">9.16</hotlnk>
                </emph>
                .
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Install the six capscrews ( two short capscrews are located at the two and three o'clock
                positions). Tighten the capscrews to the special torque value. (See
                <emph type="bold">Appendix</emph>). Refer to
                <emph type="bold">Figure
                    <hotlnk xrefid="ef1050917">9.17</hotlnk>
                </emph>
                .
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Install the vibration damper as specified in Section 7.</para>
            <figure id="ef1050916" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="eg2474" filename="../figeg2/EG2474.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 9.16.</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1>1. O-Ring</callout1>
                    <callout1>2. Dowel Mounting Position</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
            <figure id="ef1050917" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="eg2475" filename="../figeg2/EG2475.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 9.17.</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1>1. Oil Pump Housing</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
        </step1>
    </svcproc>
